4 likes, 0 comments - angelmenchan on July 7, 2024: "FORBES Sunday July 7, 2024 - MONEY AND ALEXANDER HAMILTON - 1st Secretary of Treasury of the USA under President George Washington ðŸ‡ºðŸ‡¸ 

1) George Washington on the $1 bill - 1st USA President 
2) Thomas Jefferson on the $2 bill - 3rd USA President 
3) Abraham Lincoln on the $5 bill - 16th USA President
4) Alexander Hamilton on the $10 bill - Secretary of Treasury of the USA under 1st President George Washington killed by Arron Burr * Not President 
5) Andrew Jackson on the $20 bill - 7th USA President 
6) Ulysses S. Grant on the $50 bill - 18th USA President 
7) Ben Franklin on the $100 bill - Founding Father of USA * Not President 

What about the faces on currency no longer printed? If you visit the Atlanta Fedâ€™s Monetary Museum, youâ€™ll see these bills (and more), along with the answer to that question. Notes in the denominations of $500, $1,000, $5,000, and $10,000 were last printed in 1945 but were issued through 1969. 

All these bills except one featured presidents: 

1) William McKinley on the $500 - 25th USA President 
2) Grover Cleveland on the $1,000 - 24th USA President 
3) James Madison on the $5,000 - 4th USA President 
4) Salmon Chase, a nonpresident, was featured on the $10,000 bill; he was secretary of the Treasury under President Lincoln and chief justice of the Supreme Court
5) 28th USA President Woodrow Wilson, who signed the Federal Reserve Act into law, was featured on the $100,000 gold certificate, which was used to transfer balances between Federal Reserve Banks
